text: If you are using Tensorflow 2.0 and are watching this video if you want to do  sess = tf.Session() You have to write this instead of what is above tf.compat.v1.Session(). The reason that it is like this is that in TensorFlow 2.0 does not have the same attributes as TensorFlow 1.0.  If you don't want to do the code above but don't want to install tensorflow1.0 u can import TensorFlow that has behaviors like 1.0 using this command import tensorflow.compat.v1 as tf tf.disable_v2_behavior()
